ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: good class if interested or helpful to specific research area.
Recommend to students who have interests in math and programming.
Programming-intensive course with a moderate pace and full of concepts that will prove to be useful to anyone performing modeling during their research.
I would definitely recommend ENAS 748 to anyone interested in numerical solution of ODEs or PDEs. However I would attend this course only after ENAS 747.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: gave an overall concept of dealing with related problems.
I choose this course for my own interests. It may not help a lot in my research, but it broadened my ways of thinking.

This course increased significantly my understanding in the field of numerical mathematics. Personally I found right away two applications in my research for the methods dicussed in class. Even if not applicable directly, the knowledge I gain with this course will definitely be helpful for a more appropriate use of the Matlab built-in functions that are extensively used by most of engineers in their research.
